post_text:
Good evening,

I was notified today that an employee of Minco Public Schools has tested positive for Covid-19. Due to HIPPA rules, I cannot release the name of the employee. Our thoughts and prayers are with them and their family.
This employee was at our summer pride daily. The last day was June 25th which we are still in the 14 day window for contracting and showing symptoms of the virus.
Out of an abundance of caution, the health department requests that anyone who was at summer pride the week of June 22 to 25 and is showing any symptoms should be tested for the Coronavirus, and please consult your personal physician.
Our coaches made sure the wieght room and all facilities used were sanatized thoroughly each day.
As our nation continues to work through this pandemic, we will surley have mire cases, and we must all be diligent and follow safe practices and make smart informed decisions that will help keep others safe.

God bless,
Kevin Sims

post_text:
I want to take this time to encourage my Minco family. This situation has weighed us down for several weeks now. The stress of this event can be quite heavy. We can easily be irritated and easily irritate. Frankly its hard to be confined and not live like we are to used to living. Not going to church, not going to school, not being able to see family and just not doing the normal things has gotten old for all of us. Many are losing their jobs and the stress of unemployment is hard. But, we should not lose hope. There will be an end to this. We have unified, and we will beat this. We will return to houses of worship. We will have graduation. We will have sporting events. We will have more normalcy again!! Hang tough, pray, and treat others with kindness! WHEN WE LOSE CALMNESS WITHIN OURSELVES, BE STILL AND KNOW THERE IS GOD WHO WILL CALM OUR PERSONAL STORMS!!

God bless you all,
Mr. Sims

post_text:
UPDATED INFO:
Minco Public Schools
Child Nutrition
Instructions During The School Closure

No one can go into the cafeteria other than Keystone employees and school essential personnel.
All children up to 18 years old in Minco are eligible for services.
Serving of meals will take place at the north entrance of the cafeteria located at 311 SW 6th street.
If you drive up in a car, stay in the car and meals will be delivered to you.
A child must be accompanied By an adult.
Once served, you must immediately leave and go home.
Serving times will be 8:00 to 9:00 for breakfast and 11:00 to 12:15 for Lunch
When a child is given lunch, he or she will be given breakfast for the next day to eliminate having to make two trips.

post_text:
Dear Students,
Today we went from high on the mountain to low in valley in just about 15 minutes. The feelings of disappointment were as incredible as I have felt in some time. Who would have thought the Minco would have one of the first schools affected by the Coronavirus? Not me to be honest, but I was wrong!!
While we are dissapointed, we are not defeated!! The OSSAA is planning on rescheduling at this time, but if they cannot, we are not defeated only dissapointed. I am unsure about spring sports at this time, but we are not defeated only dissapointed. I am not sure about our state conventions. If we do not get to have them, we are not defeated only dissapointed.
I have no idea what will happen this spring, but remember we are victors. We are hard workers. We are Minco Bulldogs!! Yes we are not defeated only dissappointed, and we will easily bounce back from these events!! I am so proud of your accomplishments students!! Keep working and keep living!! We will whip this Coronavirus and the sensationalism that goes with it! Bless you all!!

Mr. Sims
